en_110623_0	Sri Lankan Engineer D.A. Karunadasa who was abducted by an armed gang in Nigeria and later released, is due to arrive in the island on the 4th of this month.
en_110623_1	He was abducted in the border of Ondo and Kogi states by an armed gang on the 19th of May, after shooting the police officer who was on guard to death.
en_110623_2	Later the local Foreign Affairs Ministry and the Italian Company he worked collaborated to rescue him.
en_110623_3	It was also reported that the armed gang had demanded a ransom to release Karunadasa.
en_110623_4	68 year old Karunadasa is a resident of Mottunna in Veyangoda.
